content.description: Make easy moves past a couple of flakes in a right-facing corner to a finger crack.  Climb a short section of fingers up to a triangle-shaped roof that is hands.  Go up and over the roof to gain a nice finger crack that continues up until the crack splits.  Make delicate moves following the right-trending split via tips, thin fingers and nice pods into the chimney and a two bolt anchor.  With more traffic, this will be a great route.  A fun TR variation traverses right under the roof and continues up the chimney via wide stemming.
content.protection: BD C3-#1, #2.  C4-(2)#0.5, #2, #3.  Set of stoppers.  Two bolt rap station installed July 8, 2009.
content.location:
West end of Mighty Mouse Wall ~50 yards left of

Magna Mater Spire

.  The route is clearly visible from the highway.  See Beta photo on main page.

content.description: This is a fun, mixed route that climbs an interesting corner mostly via stemming and compression.  There are delicate crux moves just past the 2nd bolt.
content.protection: 3 bolts, red C3, #0.5 Camalot, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
It is the furthest left route on the wall.  From the base of the Magna Mater Spire, continue downhill on a well-marked trail that continues east to the base of

All Your Mite

.

content.description:
This route shares its start with

Ginger the Oppressor

and then moves left following a flared, varied crack system on the arete.
content.protection:
Standard rack plus #4 Camalot and stoppers.  2 bolt anchor at top, shares anchors with

Ginger the Oppressor

.
content.location: Same start as Ginger the Oppressor.  ~30 ft right of Magna Mater Spire.

content.description: Begin with good stemming off the ground between opposing features.  Plug in a small cam, and set sail up the right-facing corner with lots of hand jams and stems.  Climb up to a hands free stance at the bottom of a chimney, and continue up the chimney via great stems and compression passing a bolt to find the chains.
content.protection: Red C3 through wide hands, 1 QD, 2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
This is right of

Pearl Pureheart

on the backside of the lower fin.

content.description: This route climbs an easy chimney feature with great gear.  The crux comes right before the chains with an awkward mantle.
content.location:
It is right of

Mouse of the Future

on the backside of the lower fin.

content.description:
Oil Can Harry is a variation of

Quacula

.  Climb

Quacula

up to the tooth/roof feature on the left.  Pull onto the tooth and continue left into the next crack system.  Make some fun wide stems up to clip a bolt and pull onto the arete (exciting).  Traverse left and up to find the chains.
content.protection: Red C3 through 5", 1 QD.  2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
It is right of

Pearl Pureheart

on the backside of the lower fin.

content.description:
Pitch 1:  Make easy chimney moves off the ground and find a hidden #2 Camalot placement in the back of the chimney ~12 feet off the ground.  Chimney and stem up into a large pod with a handcrack on the right side of a roof.  Jam the roof and pull up to a nice flake on the left side of the chimney. Climb the hand/finger crack above to a large ledge and belay from gear (90 feet, 5.8).

Pitch 2:  Choose your own adventure in twin cracks.  The left crack is wide and a bit dirty, the right crack is fingers (recommended) with good stemming.  Belay from boulders (40 feet, 5.9).

There is some crumbly rock on this route but the climbing is varied and fun at the grade.
content.protection:
Pitch 1:  Doubles of BD # 0.75-2.0, stoppers.

Pitch 2:  BD # 0.4, 0.5, 2 and 4.  Walk off to the west.
content.location:
Route is 50 feet right of

Y-Crack

on the west end of Mighty Mouse.

content.description: This is a great route that begins in a flared, bolt protected chimney.  Chimney up to a good red C3 placement in a right-trending seam.  Continue chimneying and pass 2 bolts.  After the 2nd bolt, move right onto the face and clip a bolt.  Chimney, stem, and face climb up to a thin splitter passing another bolt.  Plug in some tiny cams, and fire the slabby headwall passing another bolt.
content.location:
This route is on the backside of the lower most fin, immediately right of

Know Your Enemy

.

climbs.name: Mind the Gap
climbs.fa: Markus Reitenbach and Alex Garhart, July 1, 2009

content.description: Climb the thin crack on the left wall of the chimney that trends deeper into the chimney (watch out for a pile of guano in a jug).  When the chimney narrows to an offwidth/squeeze, traverse back out and grunt up through the squeeze chimney (crux, protects with #6 Camalot).  Continue grunting up the squeeze to easier terrain, climb over a huge chockstone and continue up a short finger crack to a 2 bolt anchor on the right.  Shares anchors with Know Your Enemy.
content.protection: BD singles #0-3 C3, #0.4-#6 C4, set of stoppers and slings.  2 bolt anchor at top, rap 75' to the south.
content.location:
Far west end of Mighty Mouse Wall.  From the start to

Elysium

, scramble left and up to the first chimney through some scrub oak.  See Beta photo on main page.

content.description:
Make a couple tricky boulder moves off the ground to a horizontal weakness (weakness protects with BD #0.4 Camalot) and move up and right to clip a bolt using a hidden undercling.  Climb past the bolt (crux) via a sidepull and stemming to easier terrain and a good stance.  Climb easy class 5 to the unique, small summit.

This short bouldery route is very fun and would be worthy of 3 stars if it were not for the sections of slightly crumbly rock.
content.protection: BD #0.4, (2)#1, 1 bolt. No anchors on summit, down climb 8' of easy 5th class to the "neck" of formation and belay in a crack that takes #1 BDs. Simul rap from the deep groove in the neck down the east and west faces.
content.location: This free standing tower is on the far west end of Mighty Mouse Wall ~50' left of Elysium.  The route ascends the southeast arete and east face.

content.description: Start with hands off the ground and move past an offwidth pod to a good hand jam.  Pull up to into the flaring, steep offwidth.  Continue up the strenuous offwidth (crux) to a ledge.  From the ledge climb fingers and hands on the right wall of a left facing corner to the anchors.  Great stone and fun moves.
content.protection:
Singles from BD #0.5 to #5, set of stoppers.  2 bolt anchor at the top, rap 75' to the south.  Shares anchors with

Mind the Gap

.
content.location:
This route is on the far west end of Mighty Mouse Wall on the back side of the granite fin and is south facing.  15' right of

Chimneying 101

.  See Beta photo on main page.

content.description:
This route ascends double cracks with a lot of hand jamming and good climbing.  Save a small nut for the cruxy top section.

I cleaned copious amounts of bushes and dirt from this one, but it's still a bit dirty.  It should clean up with more ascents.

There is another manky pitch of 5.6 that goes to the rim.
content.protection: Fingers-wide hands, nuts, and a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
This is on the left side of the wall.  From the base of the Magna Mater Spire, continue downhill on a well-marked trail that continues east to the base of

All Your Mite

.

content.description: This route climbs a featured, well protected chimney.
content.protection:
Standard rack plus stoppers and slings.  2 bolt anchor.  Shares anchors with

Sangria Headache

.
content.location:
This route is the first chimney left of

Mind the Gap

and right of

Magna Mater Spire

.

climbs.name: Gehenna
climbs.fa: Alex Garhart and Markus Reitenbach, July 1, 2009

content.description:
Climb the first 15' of

Elysium

(crux) and traverse right 4' to the next crack around a small bulge (traverse protects with #4 Camalot and long sling).  Continue up a shallow low angle crack to a flaring offwidth (5.9) followed by a nice 5.8 hand crack.  Finish on the last 20' of

Elysium

.  The lichen on this route detracts from the overall quality but with more ascents the route will improve.
content.protection:
BD (1) #0.5, (3) #2, (3) #3, (2) #4, slings.  Shares anchors with

Elysium

.  Rap 80' to the south.
content.location:
Same start as

Elysium

on the far west end of Mighty Mouse Wall.

content.description:
This route begins with juggy face climbing up to the 2nd bolt and then turns into sustained stemming, compression, and tension moves to the 7th bolt.  Climb above the 7th bolt using a good pinch and transfer to the right over a bulge into a finger crack that leads to the chains.

This is an excellent pitch.
content.protection: 7 bolts and a couple finger-size pieces.  2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
On the far left side of the wall, look for the obvious, bolted start.

From the base of the Magna Mater Spire, continue downhill on a well-marked trail that continues east to the base of

All Your Mite

.

climbs.name: Elysium
climbs.fa: Alex Garhart and Daniel Garman, June 29, 2009

content.description: Climb big hands through a steep bulge (crux) to a good stance.  Continue up via 5.8 offwidth (#4 Camalot) into the chimney.  Climb hands in twin cracks in the back of the chimney until the cracks disappear.  Make a couple of easy chimney moves to gain another crack on the right wall of the chimney that continues to the top.
content.protection: BD (3) #2, (3-4) #3, (1-2) #4, slings.  It is best to belay from gear (#2 and #4 Camalot) and rap 80 feet down the 2-bolt station on the south side of the formation.
content.location: This route is located on the farthest west semi-detached buttres directly below Upper Mighty Mouse Wall.  Approach as if going to Upper Mighty Mouse Wall, leave the trail on your left when it intersects an obvious boulder field and traverse left across the boulders to the base of the climb.

climbs.name: Chimneying 101
climbs.fa: Markus Reitenbach and Alex Garhart, July 1, 2009

content.description: Climb a perfect hand crack for 15' in a flared corner.  Continue up with a couple of offwidth/stemming moves to the chimney.  Climb the chimney and protect in a crack on the right wall to a roof.  Pass the roof (#3 Camalot) to some more easy chimneying and top out to the left on easy terrain.
content.protection:
BD singles from #0.5 - #5 with extra #3.  Shares anchors with

Elysium

.  Rap 80' to the south.
content.location:
This is on the far west end of Mighty Mouse Wall.  Scramble up and right from start to

Elysium

to the back side of the detached fin.  Chimneying 101 is the first route on the back side.  See the Beta photo on the main page.

content.description:
Begin up a featured face past 3 bolts to gain a thin, flared crack system.  Follow thin cracks with good gear and engaging stemming up to a tooth-like feature.  From the tooth, move up and left to clip the the final bolt of

Frankenstein's Cat

, and finish in a finger crack that leads to the chains.

There is still a bit of flaky stuff coming off of this one, but it will clean up with more ascents.
content.protection:
4 bolts, set of C3s from green-yellow, small nuts, and a finger-sized cam for the finish.  There is a 2 bolt anchor which shares chains with

Frankenstein's Cat

.
content.location:
This is on the far left side of the wall.

From the base of the Magna Mater Spire, continue downhill on a well-marked trail that continues east to the base of

All Your Mite

.

climbs.name: All Your Mite
climbs.fa: T. Chamberlain, B. Chamberlain and G.  Lloyd

content.description:
Pitch 1:  Start with easy hands and face which turns into cruxy face.  Continue up the varied, overhung crack to a large ledge and belay.

Pitch 2:  Traverse up and left to a 5.8 hand crack that goes to the rim.
content.protection: Double standard rack, TCUs, small-medium wires, a couple offwidth pieces.
content.location:
This is 75 yards left of

Y Crack

.  See the beta photo on the main page.
